Road traffic fatalities in China are a pressing issue, with predictions of nearly half a million deaths annually by 2020 if action isn't taken.
The consequences are dire, as many victims are breadwinners, plunging families into poverty.
The WHO report highlights the urgency for better safety measures, improved transportation organization, and enhanced response mechanisms.
In Argentina, a seat belt crackdown led to over 2,500 tickets issued, sparking mixed reactions.
Meanwhile, in Australia, cowboy safety is questioned after a tragic incident.
Globally, road safety initiatives are being enforced, emphasizing the importance of preventive measures and public awareness.
